        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17053",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Maybe you can go into details and describe where your problem is related to ???\n\nYou created a currency from locale \"zh_TW\" with it's number formating rules and it's currency names & signs.\nThen you changed the output to be Latin script and number formating from zh_CN.\n\nBoth locales define the same number formating rules.\n\nSorry, but I don't see your problem...\nMaybe you can describe what you expect to be the output.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-10-03T06:43:10.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-10-03T06:43:10.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17054",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=liber",
                        "name": "liber",
                        "displayName": "Liber Chen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I thought it will change the currency symbol either ?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=liber",
                        "name": "liber",
                        "displayName": "Liber Chen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-10-03T09:04:43.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-10-03T09:04:43.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17055",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Not this way...\nOnce you created an currency you can not change the currency representation just with an locale.\n\nYou need to create a new currency with the expected locale or you can override the currency representation per hand with the setFormat parameters.\n\nBut toCurrency can not change the representation of the currency, only how the numbers are formatted.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-10-03T09:52:55.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-10-03T09:52:55.000+0000"
                },
                {
